{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_2e3785ba6097462195889504","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<div align=\"center\">\n2\t  <picture>\n3\t    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-dark.png?raw=true\">\n4\t    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n5\t    <img alt=\"adaptix logo\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/reagento/adaptix/v3.0.0b2/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n6\t  </picture>\n7\t\n8\t  <hr>\n9\t\n10\t  [![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/adaptix.svg?color=blue)](https://pypi.org/project/adaptix/)\n11\t  [![downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/adaptix.svg)](https://pypistats.org/packages/adaptix)\n12\t  [![versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/adaptix.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix)\n13\t  [![license](https://img.shields.io/github/license/reagento/dataclass_factory.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/master/LICENSE)\n14\t</div>\n15\t\n16\tAn extremely flexible and configurable data model conversion library.\n17\t\n18\t> [!IMPORTANT]\n19\t> Adaptix is ready for production!\n20\t> The beta version only means there may be some backward incompatible changes, so you need to pin a specific version.\n21\t\n22\t📚 [Documentation](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/)\n23\t\n24\t## TL;DR\n25\t\n26\tInstall\n27\t```bash\n28\tpip install adaptix==3.0.0b12\n29\t```\n30\t\n31\tUse for model loading and dumping.\n32\t\n33\t```python\n34\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n35\t\n36\tfrom adaptix import Retort\n37\t\n38\t\n39\t@dataclass\n40\tclass Book:\n41\t    title: str\n42\t    price: int\n43\t\n44\t\n45\tdata = {\n46\t    \"title\": \"Fahrenheit 451\",\n47\t    \"price\": 100,\n48\t}\n49\t\n50\t# Retort is meant to be global constant or just one-time created\n51\tretort = Retort()\n52\t\n53\tbook = retort.load(data, Book)\n54\tassert book == Book(title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100)\n55\tassert retort.dump(book) == data\n56\t```\n57\t\n58\tUse for converting one model to another.\n59\t\n60\t```python\n61\tfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n62\t\n63\tfrom sqlalchemy.orm import DeclarativeBase, Mapped, mapped_column\n64\t\n65\tfrom adaptix.conversion import get_converter\n66\t\n67\t\n68\tclass Base(DeclarativeBase):\n69\t    pass\n70\t\n71\t\n72\tclass Book(Base):\n73\t    __tablename__ = 'books'\n74\t\n75\t    id: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(primary_key=True)\n76\t    title: Mapped[str]\n77\t    price: Mapped[int]\n78\t\n79\t\n80\t@dataclass\n81\tclass BookDTO:\n82\t    id: int\n83\t    title: str\n84\t    price: int\n85\t\n86\t\n87\tconvert_book_to_dto = get_converter(Book, BookDTO)\n88\t\n89\tassert (\n90\t    convert_book_to_dto(Book(id=183, title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100))\n91\t    ==\n92\t    BookDTO(id=183, title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100)\n93\t)\n94\t```\n95\t\n96\t## Use cases\n97\t\n98\t* Validation and transformation of received data for your API.\n99\t* Conversion between data models and DTOs.\n100\t* Config loading/dumping via codec that produces/takes dict.\n101\t* Storing JSON in a database and representing it as a model inside the application code.\n102\t* Creating API clients that convert a model to JSON sending to the server.\n103\t* Persisting entities at cache storage.\n104\t* Implementing fast and primitive ORM.\n105\t\n106\t## Advantages\n107\t\n108\t* Sane defaults for JSON processing, no configuration is needed for simple cases.\n109\t* Separated model definition and rules of conversion\n110\t  that allow preserving [SRP](https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2014/05/08/SingleReponsibilityPrinciple.html)\n111\t  and have different representations for one model.\n112\t* Speed. It is one of the fastest data parsing and serialization libraries.\n113\t* There is no forced model representation, adaptix can adjust to your needs.\n114\t* Support [dozens](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/specific-types-behavior.html) of types,\n115\t  including different model kinds:\n116\t  ``@dataclass``, ``TypedDict``, ``NamedTuple``,\n117\t  [``attrs``](https://www.attrs.org/en/stable/), [``sqlalchemy``](https://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/20/),\n118\t  [``pydantic``](https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/) and [``msgspec``](https://jcristharif.com/msgspec/).\n119\t* Working with self-referenced data types (such as linked lists or trees).\n120\t* Saving [path](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#error-handling)\n121\t  where an exception is raised (including unexpected errors).\n122\t* Machine-readable [errors](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#error-handling)\n123\t  that could be dumped.\n124\t* Support for user-defined generic models.\n125\t* Automatic name style conversion (e.g. `snake_case` to `camelCase`).\n126\t* [Predicate system](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#predicate-system)\n127\t  that allows to concisely and precisely override some behavior.\n128\t* Disabling additional checks to speed up data loading from trusted sources.\n129\t* No auto casting by default. The loader does not try to guess value from plenty of input formats.\n130\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a06c9ad3-5660-482a-aafe-7d1e40b1f2af","uuid":"973271b6-88eb-46fe-a20a-eb7f930edf9c","timestamp":"2026-04-08T21:25:34.585Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"<div align=\"center\">\n  <picture>\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: dark)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-dark.png?raw=true\">\n    <source media=\"(prefers-color-scheme: light)\" srcset=\"https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/v3.0.0b6/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n    <img alt=\"adaptix logo\" src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/reagento/adaptix/v3.0.0b2/docs/logo/adaptix-with-title-light.png?raw=true\">\n  </picture>\n\n  <hr>\n\n  [![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/adaptix.svg?color=blue)](https://pypi.org/project/adaptix/)\n  [![downloads](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/adaptix.svg)](https://pypistats.org/packages/adaptix)\n  [![versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/adaptix.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix)\n  [![license](https://img.shields.io/github/license/reagento/dataclass_factory.svg)](https://github.com/reagento/adaptix/blob/master/LICENSE)\n</div>\n\nAn extremely flexible and configurable data model conversion library.\n\n> [!IMPORTANT]\n> Adaptix is ready for production!\n> The beta version only means there may be some backward incompatible changes, so you need to pin a specific version.\n\n📚 [Documentation](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/)\n\n## TL;DR\n\nInstall\n```bash\npip install adaptix==3.0.0b12\n```\n\nUse for model loading and dumping.\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\nfrom adaptix import Retort\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass Book:\n    title: str\n    price: int\n\n\ndata = {\n    \"title\": \"Fahrenheit 451\",\n    \"price\": 100,\n}\n\n# Retort is meant to be global constant or just one-time created\nretort = Retort()\n\nbook = retort.load(data, Book)\nassert book == Book(title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100)\nassert retort.dump(book) == data\n```\n\nUse for converting one model to another.\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import DeclarativeBase, Mapped, mapped_column\n\nfrom adaptix.conversion import get_converter\n\n\nclass Base(DeclarativeBase):\n    pass\n\n\nclass Book(Base):\n    __tablename__ = 'books'\n\n    id: Mapped[int] = mapped_column(primary_key=True)\n    title: Mapped[str]\n    price: Mapped[int]\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass BookDTO:\n    id: int\n    title: str\n    price: int\n\n\nconvert_book_to_dto = get_converter(Book, BookDTO)\n\nassert (\n    convert_book_to_dto(Book(id=183, title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100))\n    ==\n    BookDTO(id=183, title=\"Fahrenheit 451\", price=100)\n)\n```\n\n## Use cases\n\n* Validation and transformation of received data for your API.\n* Conversion between data models and DTOs.\n* Config loading/dumping via codec that produces/takes dict.\n* Storing JSON in a database and representing it as a model inside the application code.\n* Creating API clients that convert a model to JSON sending to the server.\n* Persisting entities at cache storage.\n* Implementing fast and primitive ORM.\n\n## Advantages\n\n* Sane defaults for JSON processing, no configuration is needed for simple cases.\n* Separated model definition and rules of conversion\n  that allow preserving [SRP](https://blog.cleancoder.com/uncle-bob/2014/05/08/SingleReponsibilityPrinciple.html)\n  and have different representations for one model.\n* Speed. It is one of the fastest data parsing and serialization libraries.\n* There is no forced model representation, adaptix can adjust to your needs.\n* Support [dozens](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/specific-types-behavior.html) of types,\n  including different model kinds:\n  ``@dataclass``, ``TypedDict``, ``NamedTuple``,\n  [``attrs``](https://www.attrs.org/en/stable/), [``sqlalchemy``](https://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/20/),\n  [``pydantic``](https://docs.pydantic.dev/latest/) and [``msgspec``](https://jcristharif.com/msgspec/).\n* Working with self-referenced data types (such as linked lists or trees).\n* Saving [path](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#error-handling)\n  where an exception is raised (including unexpected errors).\n* Machine-readable [errors](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#error-handling)\n  that could be dumped.\n* Support for user-defined generic models.\n* Automatic name style conversion (e.g. `snake_case` to `camelCase`).\n* [Predicate system](https://adaptix.readthedocs.io/en/latest/loading-and-dumping/tutorial.html#predicate-system)\n  that allows to concisely and precisely override some behavior.\n* Disabling additional checks to speed up data loading from trusted sources.\n* No auto casting by default. The loader does not try to guess value from plenty of input formats.\n","numLines":130,"startLine":1,"totalLines":130}}}
